description._content: Catalog #: 15_001761 Title: Macchi M.C.72 ADDITIONAL INFORMATION: Macchi M.C.72 Powered by a FIAT AS.6 V-24 engine spinning contra rotating props, this aircraft was readied for the 1931 Schneider Trophy race. Unfortunately, due to engine problems, the plane never participated. It did, however, set the world propeller driven seaplane record of just over 440 MPH back in 1934, a feat unmatched to this day. Album Name: La Coppa Schneider 1982 Collection: Charles M. Daniels Collection Photo Page #: 100 Tags: Macchi M.C.72 PUBLIC COMMONS.SOURCE INSTITUTION: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
